{"lemma":"هاجِرَةٌ","slug":"هاجِرَةٌ","root":"ه.ج.ر","root_slug":"ه-ج-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-ج-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40931","n40948"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"indecent language"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mocking speech"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"midday heat"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun formed from active participle of هَجَرَ (hajara, “to abandon”), as هَاجِر (hājir, “who abandons (person)”) + ـَة (-a)."},"ipa":["/haː.d͡ʒi.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40931","headword_ar":"هاجرهُ","root":"hjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muhaAjarapN","text_ar":"مُهَاجَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (B;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ahtjrhu","text_ar":"اهتجرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut him off from friendly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving, communion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercourse, being so cut off by him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cut him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased to speak to him, being in like manner cut by him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he forsook,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abandoned, him, being forsaken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abandoned, by him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * B:) this is the primary signification of the former. (B.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hAjr","text_ar":"هاجر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muhaAjarapN","text_ar":"مُهَاجَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijorapN","text_ar":"هِجْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an inhabitant of the desert)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went forth from his desert to the cities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towns:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is the primary acceptation, with the Arabs, of the verb [when intrans.]: also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(any one)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left his place of abode, emigrating to another people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he departed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went forth, from one land to another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from one country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town, to another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and, as used in the Kur, ii. 215, [and in many other instances in the same and other books,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emigrated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the territory of the unbelievers to the territory of the believers"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to any place of safety"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuge on account of religious persecution, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (B.) See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahaj~ara","text_ar":"تَهَجَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijorapN","text_ar":"هِجْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["A","T","Msb","K","S","Mgh","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n40948","headword_ar":"هَاجِرَةٌ","root":"hjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hujorN","text_ar":"هُجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhaAjirapu","text_ar":"الهَاجِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajiyrN","text_ar":"هَجِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajiyrapN","text_ar":"هَجِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajorN","text_ar":"هَجْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Midday when the heat is vehement:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"midday in summer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the hot season:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period from a little before noon to a little after noon in summer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the hot season, only:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, ISk:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the time when the sun declines from the meridian:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"midday, when the sun declines from the meridian, at the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zuhor","text_ar":"ظُهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its declining until the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSor","text_ar":"عَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": because people [then] shelter themselves in their tents or houses; as though they forsook one another ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahaAjaruwA","text_ar":"تَهَاجَرُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the vehemence of the heat"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhuwayojirapu","text_ar":"الهُوَيْجِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhAjrp","text_ar":"الهاجرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period a little after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAjirap","text_ar":"هَاجِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (EsSukkaree:) [pl. of the first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawaAjiru","text_ar":"هَوَاجِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabaxatohu AlhawaAjiru","text_ar":"طَبَخَتْهُ الهَوَاجِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The vehement midday heats affected him with a hot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burning, fever"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaApu Alhajiyri","text_ar":"صَلَاةُ الهَجِيرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The prayer of noon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhajiyru","text_ar":"الهَجِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", elliptically. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahiyrapN","text_ar":"ظَهِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}